00:39:36,848 --> 00:39:40,151
but they do take over.

00:39:40,151 --> 00:39:42,754
Would you be willing
to do it for 10%?

00:39:42,754 --> 00:39:44,288
10%?

00:39:44,288 --> 00:39:47,258
♪♪

00:39:47,258 --> 00:39:48,493
[ Sighs ]

00:39:50,862 --> 00:39:53,264
No, I think 20%
is good.

00:39:53,264 --> 00:39:55,266
I think 20% is right.

00:39:55,266 --> 00:39:56,968
That's one times sales.

00:39:59,270 --> 00:40:02,340
Well, Beth, let me add
some clarity to it.

00:40:04,308 --> 00:40:06,911
Her offer
is substantially better

00:40:06,911 --> 00:40:08,946
than the offer
I was gonna make.

00:40:08,946 --> 00:40:10,348
And that's just
from my experience

00:40:10,348 --> 00:40:13,284
in the baby business,
how hard it is.

00:40:13,284 --> 00:40:14,886
I'm out.

00:40:14,886 --> 00:40:16,954
John: Yeah,
let me help you, as well.

00:40:16,954 --> 00:40:18,222
I don't think I want to be

00:40:18,222 --> 00:40:20,124
in the baby‐product space
at this time.

00:40:20,124 --> 00:40:21,125
I'm out.

00:40:21,125 --> 00:40:23,261
How much of the company
do you own?

00:40:23,261 --> 00:40:24,729
I own 100% of my company.

00:40:24,729 --> 00:40:27,465
Wow. Beth, you are
the real deal.
Nice.

00:40:27,465 --> 00:40:29,700
There's no question.
I'm the real deal.

00:40:29,700 --> 00:40:31,636
I'm doing this.
I mean, you are a rock star.

00:40:31,636 --> 00:40:34,572
I don't say that very often
'cause it is tough

00:40:34,572 --> 00:40:36,974
to launch a baby product ‐‐
tough.

00:40:36,974 --> 00:40:38,609
I very much appreciate
the compliment.
Really tough, so I'm out.

00:40:38,609 --> 00:40:42,046
And you're out.
I get it. I get it.

00:40:42,046 --> 00:40:44,282
Lori ‐‐
Cuban: Don't sell yourself
short, Beth.

00:40:44,282 --> 00:40:48,853
Lori, will you do this deal
for 15%?

00:40:48,853 --> 00:40:50,688
I would love to do this
with you for 15%.

00:40:50,688 --> 00:40:53,224
I can't go past 15%.

00:40:53,224 --> 00:40:55,359
Wow.
I just can't.

00:40:55,359 --> 00:40:58,463
For me,
the bottom line would be 18%.

00:40:58,463 --> 00:40:59,597
I can't do it.
I can't.

00:40:59,597 --> 00:41:00,698
Whoa!

00:41:00,698 --> 00:41:01,999
Good for you, Beth.
I know what I've done.

00:41:01,999 --> 00:41:04,268
I love when an entrepreneur
sticks to their guns.

00:41:04,268 --> 00:41:05,903
Greiner: You could pursue it
on your own.

00:41:05,903 --> 00:41:08,506
But I don't think
that you would get as big

00:41:08,506 --> 00:41:10,741
of an up‐front
sum of money and royalty

00:41:10,741 --> 00:41:12,210
as if you're with me.

00:41:12,210 --> 00:41:14,545
Negotiating
is my sweet spot.

00:41:14,545 --> 00:41:16,981
I mean,
I'm really good at negotiating.

00:41:16,981 --> 00:41:19,584
Can you negotiate yourself
down to 15%?

00:41:19,584 --> 00:41:21,686
Yes,
what a great response!

00:41:21,686 --> 00:41:23,120
Yes!

00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:24,355
‐I love that.
‐Please.

00:41:24,355 --> 00:41:25,423
‐Oh, my goodness.
‐What a great response.

00:41:25,423 --> 00:41:26,958
‐You have 100%.
‐Please.

00:41:26,958 --> 00:41:28,893
Greiner: You have 100%
of your company.

00:41:28,893 --> 00:41:29,961
I do.

00:41:29,961 --> 00:41:33,431
If you feel the 3%
isn't worth it...

00:41:35,566 --> 00:41:37,301
It has to be
worth my time.

00:41:37,301 --> 00:41:38,903
I don't know that I would do
as well without you,

00:41:38,903 --> 00:41:40,571
but I didn't want
to go past 15%,

00:41:40,571 --> 00:41:42,507
and I had to stick to that.
I respect that.

00:41:42,507 --> 00:41:44,375
I got to stick to it
'cause I know what I've done...
I respect that.

00:41:44,375 --> 00:41:46,210
...and I know what's coming up
and I know what I can do.

00:41:46,210 --> 00:41:47,545
So are you out, Lori?

00:41:47,545 --> 00:41:50,014
Greiner: Well, listen.
15%?

00:41:50,014 --> 00:41:51,682
No, I'm sorry.

00:41:51,682 --> 00:41:53,184
Okay.

00:41:53,184 --> 00:41:55,319
Thank you for your time.

00:41:55,319 --> 00:41:56,754
Thank you, guys.
Good luck.

00:41:56,754 --> 00:41:58,089
‐Congratulations, Beth.
‐Good luck.
‐Thank you.

00:41:58,089 --> 00:41:59,423
‐Fantastic job.
‐Good luck to you.

00:41:59,423 --> 00:42:00,491
‐Thank you, guys.
‐I am rooting for you.

00:42:00,491 --> 00:42:01,659
‐Thank you.
‐Congrats, Beth.

00:42:01,659 --> 00:42:04,729
‐Thanks.
‐Fantastic.

00:42:04,729 --> 00:42:06,597
Fynbo: It's hard to walk away,
but I know the value

00:42:06,597 --> 00:42:08,366
that I'm gonna get
from the things

00:42:08,366 --> 00:42:09,901
that are upcoming for Busy Baby.

00:42:09,901 --> 00:42:11,702
Lori would have been
amazing to work with.

00:42:11,702 --> 00:42:13,037
She really would have been.

00:42:13,037 --> 00:42:15,806
I'm very confident
in myself and my plans

00:42:15,806 --> 00:42:17,842
and what I'm doing,
and I really think I can do it.

00:42:17,842 --> 00:42:19,810
I just wasn't willing
to give up 18%.

